default2. How best to filter out extremist material, including images of child abuse and material intended to promote terrorism or other acts of violence?default&#xa0;
defaultWhen children start to hit puberty
default,
default then without places where they can talk about sex in a positive way (and not just mechanics) then they will go looking for potentially harmful images, and in the world we live in it is virtually impossible to censor those completely.”
default 
defaultYoung person, 18.
default&#xa0;
default2.1 
defaultAny proposal to restrict young people’s access to extreme material online will be fraught with complication and difficult to implement. Filters must be sophisticated to allow for a range of factors (for example, households with children of different ag
defaultes, and differing definitions of pornography). Part of supporting young people through education is ensuring they have access to good quality, factual information on sexual health online. Attempts to restrict young people’s access to pornography may inadve
defaultrtently lead to the blocking of good quality education sites. 
default&#xa0;
default2.2 
defaultAlthough y
defaultoung people have told us that while they are concerned about pornography and would like help and support dealing with it, we must 
defaultalso 
defaultacknowledge that a block can only go so far
default and as discussed in our response to Question 1, we should ensure we 
defaultpromote the need for
default education for young people and support for parents at the same time.
default&#xa0;
defaultDefining ‘extremist’
default&#xa0;
default2.3 
defaultBrook and FPA support the views of the young people interviewed by 
defaultBrook
default and that it is 
defaultimportant to give consideration to what is deemed 
default‘
defaultextremist
default’
default. They were clear that images of child abuse or bestiality should be banned, but some felt that censoring images of bondage, for example, is wrong because acts of bondage may
default be consensual. They were clear that there is a huge difference between sexual violence and consensual acts of bondage. There was also concern from young people who identify as LGB
default and 
defaultT that some of the porn they can relate to might be labeled as “extremi
defaultst” whereas in fact porn involving
default, for example,
default trans* individuals often reinforces their identity and sense of self, rather than being fetishistic. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAddressing the issue at the source
default&#xa0;
default2.4 
defaultSome of the young people 
defaultthat Brook
default spoke with 
defaultalso 
defaultfelt that 
defaultresponsibility should be placed on the websites which host extreme materials. Rather than being an issue of filters, the issue should be addressed at the source.
default&#xa0;
default“Surely the issue should be with the websites themselves existing, rather than blocking out young people's free will to surf the web. We should be tackling the websites themselves, rather than blocking access to them...” 
defaultYoung person, 20.
default&#xa0;
default“Make the promot
defaultion and creation of website such as these illegal and ensure that it's an offence that the police take active force to enforce.” 
defaultYoung person, 23.
default&#xa0;
default2.5 
defaultFurthermore, Brook 
defaultand FPA 
defaultwould like to point out that although online pornography will almost always 
defaultshow consenting adults, it rarely shows that the consent leading to the actions being undertaken has been pre-discussed and negotiated. This leads to a perception that it is somehow acceptable to quickly engage in sexual acts that others may find extreme, 
defaultwithout gaining the permission of all parties involved. Brook
default and FPA 
defaultrecommend that the perception of 
defaultthis needs
default to change, and 
defaultthe
default Government 
defaultshould implement 
defaultpolicy which leads to pornography websites showing the consent and negotiation that leads to the sexual acts which are shown. 
